          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-16 15:35:36" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>act of destroying or causing the destruction of persons, objects, or institutions</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>destruction</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages it is difficult to find a general term for ‘destruction.’ What has often happened is the extension of meaning from a more specific type of reference, for example, ‘to smash,’ to a more generic meaning of ‘to destroy,’ and whether one understands the specific or more generic meaning depends largely upon the context. Accordingly, in {S:04400800300006} one may find a figurative usage of a term meaning ‘to smash’ (though understood in a more generic sense), for example, ‘Saul then worked in order to smash the church.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
